 South Africa has a total of 12 739 confirmed Covid-19 cases according to an announcement by minister of health, Dr Zweli Mkhize, on Thursday May 14. A total of 67 of those cases have been recorded in Mpumalanga. According to data released by the Mpumalanga Department of Health, 34 recoveries have been recorded to date. There have been no deaths recorded in Mpumalanga. • Bushbuckridge: 1 case and 1 recovery
• City of Mbombela: 13 cases and 7 recoveries
• Nkomazi: 20 cases and 12 recoveries
